        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 4:41AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 440 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 13 miles east of Gatlinburg to 3 miles south of
Robbinsville. An isolated thunderstorm could develop within
the line of showers. Movement was east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dillsboro, Wesser, Stecoah, Smoky Mountains-Newfound Gap, Smoky
Mountains-Fontana Area, Nantahala, Lake Santeetlah, Deals Gap, Smoky
Mountains-Balsam Mountain, and Fontana Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
these storms pass.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM EDT for western North
Carolina.</instruction>
